# Three Tasks: Notification Migration + Mobile Spotlight + Mobile Audit

## Task 1 — Notification Migration
Run `npx supabase db push` to deploy `20260505000000_message_notification_preview.sql`.
This creates the `update_message_notification_preview` RPC that patches encrypted notification bodies with real plaintext after a message is sent.

## Task 2 — Hero Spotlight on Mobile (Touch Support)
**File:** `src/components/HeroPattern.tsx`

`mousemove` doesn't fire on touch screens. Add `touchmove` + `touchend` alongside the existing mouse handlers:
- `touchmove`: read `e.touches[0].clientX/Y`, set `--mx`/`--my` same as mouse
- `touchend`: reset to `50% 50%` same as mouseleave
- Use `{ passive: true }` on the touchmove listener for scroll performance

## Task 3 — Full Mobile Responsiveness Audit
Audit and fix issues across all main pages and layout components. Focus areas:
- **Navigation**: TopBar, MobileBottomNav, ProfileDrawer — tap targets, overflow
- **Home**: Hero CTA buttons full-width on mobile, feature card grid
- **Pricing**: Plan cards, toggle switches, FAQ section
- **About**: Gallery scroll, events section, founder section
- **CreviaStudio**: Tab bar horizontal scroll, dialog/sheet sizes
- **Dialogs & Sheets**: All dialogs need `max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto`, full-width on small screens
- **Forms**: Input/textarea padding on mobile keyboards
- **Typography**: Ensure no text overflows containers on 320px screens

## Execution Order
1. Run migration (supabase db push)
2. Touch support in HeroPattern.tsx
3. Mobile audit pass — fix issues found page by page
